  "original_description": "Small-task implementation with gate-enforced TDD. Trigger immediately when: (1) the user gives a casual go-ahead after issues or fixes have been identified \u2014 \u300c\u4e00\u8d77\u8655\u7406\u5427\u300d\u300c\u76f4\u63a5\u6539\u300d\u300c\u53bb\u505a\u300d\u300c\u5e6b\u6211\u4fee\u300d\u300c\u597d\u5c31\u9019\u6a23\u300d\u300c\u53ef\u4ee5\u4e86\u300dor any equivalent confirmation; (2) the user selects an option from a presented list of fixes or choices \u2014 \"A - 2\", \"\u9078 1\", \"Option 2\", \"\u7b2c\u4e00\u500b\", or any short pick after options were shown; (3) a concrete task arrives directly or is handed off from /think with an approved plan; (4) scope is clear and fits one session. Builds a TaskCreate checklist upfront, executes Red\u2192Green with hard gates, then passes to /baransu:review. Cosmetic-only changes (comments, dead imports, renames, formatting) skip Red/Green and go straight to review. User-facing output in Traditional Chinese (\u7e41\u9ad4\u4e2d\u6587).",
